<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>阿里云 on Margrop Blog</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/tag/%E9%98%BF%E9%87%8C%E4%BA%91/</link><description>Recent content in 阿里云 on Margrop Blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 30 Jan 2021 15:33:44 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.margrop.net/en/tag/%E9%98%BF%E9%87%8C%E4%BA%91/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>How to Configure a Freshly Installed Ubuntu 20.04 Server VM on PVE</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/pve-how-to-config-brand-new-ubuntu-20.04-vm/</link><pubDate>Sat, 30 Jan 2021 15:33:44 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/pve-how-to-config-brand-new-ubuntu-20.04-vm/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="download-the-installation-iso"&gt;Download the Installation ISO&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu-releases/focal/ubuntu-20.04.2-live-server-amd64.iso"&gt;Aliyun Ubuntu 20.04 live server download&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="https://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu-releases/bionic/ubuntu-18.04.5-live-server-amd64.iso"&gt;Aliyun Ubuntu 18.04 live server download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Upgrading or Fresh Installing MariaDB 10.5 on CentOS 7 Using Aliyun Mirror</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/centos-7-upgrade-or-install-mariadb-10.x-aliyun-mirror/</link><pubDate>Fri, 29 Jan 2021 15:42:20 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/centos-7-upgrade-or-install-mariadb-10.x-aliyun-mirror/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="update-the-system-first"&gt;Update the System First&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;yum update -y
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id="edit-the-yum-configuration-file-using-aliyun-mirror"&gt;Edit the yum Configuration File Using Aliyun Mirror&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Here MariaDB 10.5 is used as an example&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;vim /etc/yum.repos.d/MariaDB10.repo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#http://downloads.mariadb.org/mariadb/repositories/&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;mariadb&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; MariaDB
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;baseurl &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; https://mirrors.aliyun.com/mariadb/yum/10.5/centos7-amd64
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gpgkey &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; https://mirrors.aliyun.com/mariadb/yum/RPM-GPG-KEY-MariaDB
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gpgcheck &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Installing Docker on CentOS 7 and Configuring Aliyun Mirror Source</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/centos-7-install-docker-ce-and-update-source/</link><pubDate>Fri, 29 Jan 2021 11:40:18 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/centos-7-install-docker-ce-and-update-source/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="docker-version"&gt;Docker Version&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since Docker version 1.13, Docker has adopted a timeline-based versioning approach, dividing releases into Community Edition (CE) and Enterprise Edition (EE). Docker CE is the free community edition, while Docker EE is the paid enterprise version.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Installing the Latest Version of Node and NPM on CentOS 7</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/centos-7-install-node-and-npm-latest/</link><pubDate>Wed, 27 Jan 2021 11:28:59 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/centos-7-install-node-and-npm-latest/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="downloading-node"&gt;Downloading Node:&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The download uses the Aliyun mirror&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir ~/nodejs
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd ~/nodejs
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://npm.taobao.org/mirrors/node/latest-v15.x/node-v15.7.0-linux-x64.tar.gz
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;tar -xvzf node-v15.7.0-linux-x64.tar.gz
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>